#

Since we cannot put folders in workflows, the workflows will need to be named appropriately instead.

All workflows should be prefixed with
type-concern-function-<-script-name.yml>

where:
type: the category of script or action it belongs to
=[automation, audit, dispatch, generate, remediate, validate, interface]
concern: what part of the system the workflow operates on.
= [copy, governance, documentation, ]
function: what this script does
=[update, nonitor, ]

eg. update-contract-addresses.yaml
-> update is the function (we should enum these also)
-> type is automation
-> concern is content (what is the scipt definitions of this?)

automation-content-update-contract-addresses.yml

